A 44-year-old man, Fayemi Shadrack, on Monday appeared at an
Ikorodu Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly obtaining N1.35 million under
false pretence. He pleaded not guilty to the three-count charge of
conspiracy, stealing and obtaining money under false pretence. Prosecuting Sergeant John Iberedem said the defendant
committed the offence last December at 6, Ademibuyon Street, Agbede Ebuwawa,
Owutu, Ikorodu. He alleged that Shadrack conspired with one person, who is
at large, to fraudulently obtain N1.35 million from the complainant, Imocha
Benedict. Chief Magistrate F. A. Azeez granted the defendant N200, 000
bail with two sureties in the like sum. She adjourned till September 15.